title: Campaign for high speed train on South Coast gathers pace
text:
The high speed 'Javelin' train Credit: ITV News Meridian The campaign to bring high speed rail to the South East coast is gaining pace, as councils get set to publish a report on the potential economic benefits.
The specialist research investigates the possible financial impact of extending the HS1 'Javelin' service from Ashford to Hastings.
Last updated Fri 9 Oct 2015 Travel train High speed rail Sussex
